Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrots{2} then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons. Trim and halve the @radishes{100%g}. Pop the carrots and radishes onto another large baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While everything cooks, halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(halved and chopped) into small pieces. Roughly chop the @chives{1}(roughly chopped).

> Use scissors for easier chopping.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Season the @British pork loin steaks{2} with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Once hot, add the pork steaks to the #pan{}. Cook until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Reduce the heat to medium and fry for an additional ~{6-8%minutes}, turning every couple of mins. Once cooked, remove to a #plate{} and cover with another plate or #foil{} to rest.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the pork rests, pop your (now empty) pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. When hot, add the @red onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped) and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the @water{75%ml}, @Dijon mustard{15%g} and @chicken stock paste{1%tsp}, then bring to the boil. Simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir through the @creme fraiche{75%g} and half the chives, bring back to the boil, then remove from the heat.

Once your veggies are roasted, drizzle the @honey{15%g} over the carrots and radishes, then stir to coat.

> If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Slice the pork steaks widthways, then serve on plates with the honeyed veg and roast potatoes alongside. Spoon over the sauce and finish with a sprinkle of the remaining chives.